data.name: StringTable.MessageFormat_WhenTheTruckHasStoppedAdjustingRemainsStillAndIsNoLongerRestsOnTheStandardHeightGaugeBlocks
data.value: When the truck has stopped adjusting, remains still, and no longer rests on the Standard Height Gauge Blocks, remove the Standard Height Gauge Blocks. Then, place Aero Height Gauge Blocks on {0}. To ensure correct location reference the help guide. Once gauge blocks are in place the suspension will release air until the truck is resting on gauge blocks. After calibration is stored the truck will automatically raise.

data.name: StringTable.Message_HeightValuesHaveBeenStored
data.value: The height values have been stored. Go to the Aerodynamic Height Control Test Panel in the Actions Tab. Using the test panel, set the truck into Aero Mode. The Aero Height Blocks should fit between the frame rail and axle with clearance. Next, using the test panel, set the truck into Standard Mode. The Standard Height Blocks should fit between the frame rail and axle with clearance. Once heights are verified, calibration has been complete.

data.name: StringTable.Message_TruckIsCurrentlyLoweringStep5Instructions
data.value:
Truck is currently lowering. Once the truck has stopped moving, please do a visual inspection:
Inspect Center Axle. Frame rail should be making contact with bump stop. Use the Center Axle Inspection picture as a reference.
Inspect Front Axle. Frame rail should NOT be making contact with the bump stops. Touch airbag to verify that it is deflated. Use the Front Axle Inspection picture as a reference.
Once Inspection is complete, click next.
